  </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Girl(shiny) with Sniper Rifle</span><hr size=1> I've heard of a .22 being used in the military as a sniper round (not so much in police, the gangs like them but not the police). The difference is it is usually a .22 mag or hornet. Usually they are used at close range (ex. in a city) where the sniper needs to be able to shoot a lot fast with either no report (suppress the rifle) or a little bit of report that is confusing. .22 cal will also be used when richochet and wall penitration is a concern.<br>
But this is an extremely rare occurance this happens. .22 is not a good person round unless at close range and it is a head shot. Espefcially being that all armor and helmets in the world will stop this round. Usually a M4, M16, or G3A3 (5.56 NATO/.223 Remington) using hollow point rounds would be outfitted with a sniper package for this role instead. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uburncycle360.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Burncycle360</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/15/01 5:13:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4108.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Girl(shiny) with Sniper Rifle</span><hr size=1> I believe it's .22 magnum, and yes, it's in urban areas. <br>
<br>
The advantages are 1) its very lightweight 2) Its easy to carry around (and lots of ammo) 3) Its QUIET in the first place, and easily silenced.<br>
<br>
The Israelis use it for sure, not sure about anyone else.<br>
<br>
The key here is, you can WOUND someone with a .22<br>
You don't HAVE to kill him. Thats the advantage. Think about it. One guy is wounded, it takes one-two people to carry him out of the line of fire to get medican attention. Thats 3 people out of action at least temporarily. And him screaming in pain isn't going to help their morale either. If you kill the guy, not only do they not need to carry him off (thus they can stay and fight) but often times you increase their will to fight.  Plus, doesen't matter if he dies or not, he isn't going to be fighting back with a center mass or head wound. <br>
<br>
Obviously not a rifle used for assasination where you want to kill your target. But its quite effective as a harrassment weapon (and really messes up enemy morale).<br>
<br>
The .22 sniper rifles are suppressed and can effectively take out barking dogs (before an attack), they can also disable protest or riot leaders without killing them.<br>
<br>
<br>
Here's a .22 sniper <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.waronline.org/IDF/pictures/Smallarms/pages/image7.htm">www.waronline.org/IDF/pic...image7.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
<br>
What I would like to see is a Five seveN sniper rifle. Shooting the 5.7mm ammunition. Its just as easily silenced as a .22, and it penetrates body armor without overpenetrating, and does massive amounts of internal damage. Would also be short ranged so it would have to be used in an urban environment too. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uburncycle360.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Burncycle360</A> at: 12/15/01 5:14:49 am<br></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#336699>- </font><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs>Polykarbon BBS</a><font color=#336699> - </font><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm13>Black and White Art</a> <font color=#336699> - </font><a href="http://www.polykarbon.com">Polykarbon: Manga & Photoshop</a><font color=#336699> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.4 b8<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  